messages.text: SafeHaven chat. 02/15/17 11:14 AM.
Lyle Hewitt is connected.
Dr. Took is connected.
Hello, Dr. Took. Thank you for being on time to your performance review.
Hello, Mr. Hewitt.
I have looked over your recent statistics.
I am pleased to see that two of your existing customers have reenrolled for another three months of services.
Thank you.
I take it you have given due thought to our conversation about customer retention rates?
Yes.
Good.
Keep in mind that your first six months with SafeHaven is a probationary period.
It is imperative that you follow management's direction and recommendations regarding retention.
Of course.
Tell me how your homicidal customer is doing, please.
Please refer to him as a patient.
Or a client.
Apologies.
How is your homicidal client doing?
He needs a higher level of care.
I have communicated to him that he should be evaluated by a medical doctor in addition to his treatment with me.
And has he been to a doctor?
No. He refused.
I requested that he call me after he disconnected suddenly during our last session.
He has not responded.
When was your last session with him?
Thursday, February 9.
Our next session is scheduled for tomorrow afternoon at 1:15.
He contacted you for the appointment time?
No. We scheduled session times in advance.
I see.
Please keep me informed of his progress.
Of course.
I have spoken to your clinical supervisor, Dr. Abbott.
I am concerned about your ability to treat the client in question.
Why?
What did she tell you?
Dr. Abbott informed me that you have had a life experience that could make it difficult for you to empathize with the client.
You are referring to my husband.
Yes.
Dr. Abbott told me he was killed by a drunk driver.
Yes.
Four years ago.
She said your client has been involved in a drunk driving fatality.
Clinical supervision is supposed to be confidential.
Dr. Abbott is required to divulge information that could affect your quality of treatment.
My husband's death does not affect my work, Mr. Hewitt.
Tell me about your husband.
No.
He was in law enforcement, correct?
A police officer?
He was a homicide detective.
How long had you been married before the accident?
Two years.
I see.
And how does it make you feel when you discuss drunk driving with patientzero?
I assume that Dr. Abbott already told you how I feel.
She did.
But I'd like to hear it from you.
I am not at liberty to discuss my patients outside of clinical supervision.
I find this all rather unethical.
But I'm asking about you, Dr. Took.
How do you feel?
I feel like I need to report patientzero to get him more help.
Dr. Abbott advised you to continue to treat him, did she not?
Yes, she did.
She will be keeping an eye on your discussions with patientzero to ensure you are providing him with quality care.
And she has advised you to ask him again for his personal information.
Yes.
But I think he is a danger to himself and others.
His brother, in particular.
I feel sure that we can find a way to keep your client safe as well as protect his privacy.
However, I am currently receiving an important phone call, Dr. Took, that I'm afraid I must take.
You have a few other clients I'd like to discuss as well.
May we continue your review this afternoon?
Of course.
Good. I will be in touch.
Lyle Hewitt is disconnected.
Dr. Took is disconnected.
SafeHaven chat. 02/15/17 9:08 PM.
patientzero is connected.
Hi, Dr. Took.
I need to talk to you soon.
He found the mugshot.
Dr. Took is connected.
Hi, patientzero.
I'm glad you reached out to me.
My brother found the mugshot.
He got on my computer while I was taking a shower.
Probably to look at porn.
But he saw my search history.
Did he talk to you about it?
No.
I wouldn't say he talked.
What do you mean?
He cold cocked me.
He yanked me out of the shower by my hair and yelled at me.
He said he found it and that I needed to get the fuck over it.
Then he hit me.
Are you OK?
Do you need a doctor?
I'm OK.
I don't think I have a concussion or anything.
I'd feel better about it if you were seen by a doctor.
You'd feel better?
Yes. I am concerned about you.
I shouldn't have had him over.
Why did you?
I guess I thought if we could hang out and get along that things could get better between us.
Like they were before the accident.
Has he ever been violent to you before?
Yeah, and I've done shit to him, too.
But we weren't ever like this.
Like what, patientzero?
Afraid of each other.
Like I said, we've got our problems. But this is at a whole new level.
How would you like to proceed in therapy at this point?
How can I better help you?
I don't know.
I guess I still need to talk to somebody.
Are you still feeling guilty?
Yeah.
I mean, how would you feel if you killed someone?
How would you feel if it had been someone you loved who got killed?
Like your sister?
Or your husband?
What do you know about my husband?
Nothing.
I guess I just assumed you were married.
That's all.
I see.
I didn't mean to offend you.
You didn't offend me. It's OK.
I've seen your photo on your profile page.
You are very pretty.
Thank you.
I've never had a girlfriend before.
Why do you think that is?
I'm not good at talking to people.
You talk to me just fine, patientzero.
But it's not like you'd want to go out with me.
Why do you say that?
I don't know. Would you?
It's unethical to date a patient.
But I think the question speaks volumes about how you think of yourself.
It's worth exploring more.
I think about you a lot.
Perhaps you feel connected to me because this is a safe space where you can speak without judgment.
That's a great thing in therapy.
Are you actually married, Hortence?
I'd like you to call me Dr. Took, please.
And your therapy isn't about me.
If I were in your office with you, I could see if you are wearing a ring or not.
I don't really know anything about you.
Your therapy is focused on you, patientzero.
I am here to help you feel better.
I feel worse now.
Why do you feel worse?
You rejected me.
I am sorry you feel like that, patientzero.
But I have to adhere to ethical policies for my profession.
You sound like a robot again.
That is not my intention.
I care very much about your well-being.
The boundaries are there for your protection.
I should go.
Will I speak to you at our session tomorrow?
Yeah.
I guess.
If my brother doesn't kill me first.
patientzero is disconnected.
Dr. Took is disconnected.

And the obituary.
I know what happened to your husband.
